w1.notes:
* Despite ''Spirit Cleave'' generally hitting targets' {{tip|edge range}}, it ''cannot'' hit targets whose center is behind him.
** This behaviour is common with [[Projectile|missiles]], however some cone spells such as this one also do it.
* ''Spirit Cleave'' will not benefit from the bonus attack speed gained by {{ri|Hail of Blades}}.{{bug}}
* {{tip|Spell shield}} does not prevent '''Yone''' from receiving and/or increasing the {{tip|shield}}.
* The shield's amount will also increase for each {{tip|clone}} hit.
{{Effect at cast time end}}
** '''Yone''' will always cast ''Spirit Cleave'' in his facing direction, and he will turn to face the target direction at the start of the cast time.
* The mixed damage is applied in two instances, and the {{as|physical damage}} will be dealt first within the same game tick.
** If the {{as|physical damage}} finishes off the unit, the {{as|magic damage}} will not be dealt against it.{{bug}}

e1.notes:
* The ''marks'' store {{tip|physical damage}}, {{tip|magic damage}}, and {{tip|true damage}}.
* ''Soul Unbound'' stays on cooldown for the first 15 seconds of the game.
<!--Spirit Form-->
* {{si|Recall}} and {{si|Teleport}} are disabled during ''Soul Unbound''.
* Only '''Yone's''' initial dash can be {{tip|interrupt|interrupted}}.
* '''Yone's''' orange [[resource]] bar during ''Soul Unbound'' is indicative of the amount of time '''Yone''' has to recast the ability before it is automatically recast. The amount starts at 500 and rapidly decays down to 0. It counts down from the start of the cast, not after the {{fd|0.5}}-second delay.
** With {{fd|0.5}} seconds remaining before the recast occurs automatically, a distinct sound will cue and the corners of the screen will briefly turn a faint dark. This is only visible and audible to '''Yone'''.
* '''Yone's''' body unit cannot be interacted with by any means. It will despawn as soon as '''Yone's''' dash back ends.
<!--Recast-->
* ''Soul Unbound's'' recast, even when cast automatically, counts as an ability activation for the purposes of on-cast effects such as {{tip|Spellblade}} and stacking {{ai|Force Pulse|Kassadin}}.
* ''Soul Unbound's'' recast does not interrupt '''Yone's''' last movement or attack order.
* '''Yone''' will place himself onto the ground and interrupts {{tip|airborne|displacements}} affecting him upon recasting.
* ''Soul Unbound's'' recast is notable for being an ability that {{tip|cleanse|removes}} {{tip|crowd control}} but cannot be activated while unable to cast abilities or mobility spells due to the same crowd control.
* '''Yone''' will not resist the {{tip|suspension}} from {{ai|Aqua Prison|Nami}} during the recast's cast time.{{bug|2}}
* ''Soul Unbound'' does '''not''' {{tip|cleanse}} the following {{tip|crowd control}} effects (ones not listed below are removed):
** {{tip|Disarm}}
*** Only the {{tip|silence}} portion from {{tip|polymorph}} will be removed.
** {{tip|Ground}}
** {{tip|Nearsight}}
** {{tip|Silence}}
** {{tip|Slow}}
*** {{ai|Wither|Nasus}} will not be removed.
* Some examples of effects that can delay ''Soul Unbound's'' automatic recast:
** {{tip|Attack windup}}
** [[Channel#Casting Times|Cast time]]
** {{tip|Channel|Channels}} (excluding {{si|Hexflash}})
** {{tip|Lockout|Lockouts}}
** {{tip|Dash|Dashes}}
** {{tip|Immobilize|Immobilizes}}, {{tip|Silence}}, {{tip|Ground}}, and {{tip|Stasis}}
** {{ai|Devour|Tahm Kench}}
** {{ai|Fate's Call|Kalista}}
*** '''Yone''' instantly appears at his body's location the moment this effect ends.
** {{ai|Realm Warp|Ryze}}
* ''Soul Unbound's'' recast is disabled (cannot be manually nor automatically cast) while '''Yone''' is in the {{ai|Realm of Death|Mordekaiser}} or is trapped in {{ai|The Hextech Ultimatum|Camille}}. The recast will be deferred until he has escaped.
** The recast may still be buffered to cast during other certain effects (such as {{ai|Fate Sealed|Yone}}) despite being disabled, thus being able to escape those two abilities.{{bug}}
*** {{ai|The Hextech Ultimatum|Camille}} will specifically end if '''Yone''' recasts ''Soul Unbound'' while he's trapped.
* If '''Yone''' uses {{ai|Mortal Steel|Yone}} at two ''Gathering Storm'' stacks to delay ''Soul Unbound's'' automatic recast, he will be able to basic attack once in a short time period before the automatic recast triggers.
* If '''Yone''' {{tip|death|dies}} or enters {{tip|resurrection}} with ''Spirit Form'', he will immediately initiate the recast and dash back to his body while dead or resurrecting.
** If he dies during the recast, the dash back is not interrupted.
** His death animation will play upon arriving to his body.
* '''Yone''' will not be locked out nor will he be {{tip|displacement immune}} during the dash back if he becomes displaced during the recast's cast time (e.g. through {{ai|Devour|Tahm Kench}}, {{ai|Fear Beyond Death 2|Urgot|Fear Beyond Death}}, {{ai|Aqua Prison|Nami}}, or {{uis|Baron Nashor}} [[Baron_Nashor_(League_of_Legends)#Passives|Presence of the Baron]]).{{bug|2}}
<!--Damage-->
* The marks do not store damage from [[item]]s, [[rune]]s and [[summoner spell]]s.
* The mark also automatically detonates without '''Yone''' having to recast when the marked champion dies or enters {{tip|resurrection}}.
* The detonation damage cannot be dodged by becoming {{tip|untargetable}}.
* The marks will not store damage dealt to {{tip|shield|shields}}.
* If the mark's damage is higher than the target's '''current''' health, the mark indicator will have a slightly different appearance.
